00:00:11,580 --> 00:00:13,340
Be careful out there.

4
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:14,180
Don't worry.

5
00:00:17,580 --> 00:00:18,100
Changfeng,

6
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:18,980
this is far enough.

7
00:00:20,540 --> 00:00:21,740
Always keep

8
00:00:22,140 --> 00:00:24,020
Xing's Precepts in mind.

9
00:00:24,660 --> 00:00:24,900
Got it.

10
00:00:24,900 --> 00:00:26,020
It's what Master demands.

11
00:00:26,420 --> 00:00:27,820
And also what we need
for our own discipline.

12
00:00:28,100 --> 00:00:28,900
Alright.

13
00:00:30,060 --> 00:00:30,940
You still remember them?

14
00:00:31,380 --> 00:00:32,180
Yeah.

15
00:00:32,980 --> 00:00:34,020
Like the back of my hand.

16
00:00:34,820 --> 00:00:35,780
Recite them then.

17
00:00:38,020 --> 00:00:39,100
Do not kill.

18
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:40,660
Do not

19
00:00:40,660 --> 00:00:42,220
corner another into the empty end.

20
00:00:42,380 --> 00:00:43,260
It's the "dead end".

21
00:00:43,700 --> 00:00:44,580
Into the dead end?

22
00:00:45,180 --> 00:00:45,580
Alright.

23
00:00:45,780 --> 00:00:46,340
Do not

24
00:00:46,380 --> 00:00:47,660
corner another into the dead end.

25
00:00:48,140 --> 00:00:50,380
Do not harm the elderly, weak,
sick, or the disabled.

26
00:00:50,940 --> 00:00:52,180
The elderly, weak,
disabled, or the sick.

27
00:00:52,740 --> 00:00:53,540
Close enough.

28
00:00:54,220 --> 00:00:56,460
Do not... Do not fight among our own.

29
00:00:56,820 --> 00:00:58,660
Do not clash with the authorities.

30
00:00:59,340 --> 00:01:01,740
Do not use our skills

31
00:01:01,900 --> 00:01:03,820
to profit in other ways.

32
00:01:04,580 --> 00:01:05,380
Am I right?

33
00:01:06,060 --> 00:01:06,940
Pretty much.

34
00:01:08,420 --> 00:01:09,380
Master said

35
00:01:09,860 --> 00:01:11,380
though you came to this craft midway,

36
00:01:11,380 --> 00:01:12,340
with the skills you already had,

37
00:01:13,260 --> 00:01:14,740
you've shown real talent.

38
00:01:15,220 --> 00:01:16,300
Other disciples

39
00:01:16,460 --> 00:01:17,940
take six years of dedicated training

40
00:01:18,540 --> 00:01:19,620
before they can finish the training.

41
00:01:19,940 --> 00:01:21,300
But you did it in three.

42
00:01:21,740 --> 00:01:23,020
Master is proud.

43
00:01:25,260 --> 00:01:26,340
The journey ahead is long.

44
00:01:27,420 --> 00:01:28,740
No matter where life takes you,

45
00:01:29,140 --> 00:01:29,940
I hope

46
00:01:29,940 --> 00:01:31,380
you'll always keep Xing's Precepts

47
00:01:31,900 --> 00:01:32,820
in your mind.

48
00:01:33,340 --> 00:01:33,820
I will.

49
00:01:35,460 --> 00:01:36,100
Changfeng,

50
00:01:36,740 --> 00:01:37,780
please tell Master

51
00:01:38,340 --> 00:01:39,100
I will always

52
00:01:39,540 --> 00:01:40,620
remember his teachings

53
00:01:41,140 --> 00:01:41,900
and never bring shame to you all.

54
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:45,580
Alright. Head back now.

55
00:01:45,620 --> 00:01:47,140
Master needs someone by his side.

56
00:01:48,340 --> 00:01:48,740
Alright.

57
00:02:03,740 --> 00:02:04,380
Take care.

58
00:02:04,780 --> 00:02:06,060
Just wait. I'm gonna

59
00:02:06,420 --> 00:02:07,260
make it big.

60
00:02:52,140 --> 00:02:55,060
[Double Track Puzzle]

61
00:02:55,060 --> 00:03:01,100
[Adapted from Zhao Junkai's novel,
Double Track Puzzle]

62
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:05,580
[Episode 9]

63
00:03:11,660 --> 00:03:13,180
I'll give you this one chance.

64
00:03:13,460 --> 00:03:14,900
What happened

65
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:16,460
to my three batches of goods?

66
00:03:16,460 --> 00:03:17,380
Spell it out.

67
00:03:18,380 --> 00:03:20,460
If I hear one word that doesn't add up,

68
00:03:21,060 --> 00:03:22,740
you're both die here.

69
00:03:23,420 --> 00:03:23,980
Mr. Sun,

70
00:03:24,940 --> 00:03:26,620
the first batch was hidden
by Zheng Xiaoshan.

71
00:03:27,020 --> 00:03:28,140
We never found it.

72
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:29,460
The second

73
00:03:29,820 --> 00:03:30,620
got snatched on the train

74
00:03:30,620 --> 00:03:32,140
by those from the northern frontier.

75
00:03:33,980 --> 00:03:35,460
This batch must've been taken
by them too.

76
00:03:38,100 --> 00:03:38,780
And, Mr. Sun,

77
00:03:39,420 --> 00:03:40,820
our guy who went to pick up
the goods on the train

78
00:03:41,300 --> 00:03:42,580
got caught by the cops.

79
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:47,940
You think I'm stupid?

80
00:03:50,100 --> 00:03:52,100
What are they, clairvoyant?

81
00:03:52,180 --> 00:03:53,220
How could they possibly know

82
00:03:53,220 --> 00:03:54,620
when we were picking up the goods?

83
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:56,180
And how could they know

84
00:03:56,180 --> 00:03:57,500
exactly where?

85
00:03:58,180 --> 00:03:58,740
Mr. Sun,

86
00:03:59,980 --> 00:04:01,140
look at us.

87
00:04:01,460 --> 00:04:02,900
We've got no reason to lie to you.

88
00:04:03,380 --> 00:04:04,020
Could it be

89
00:04:05,100 --> 00:04:06,580
that the supplier's setting us up?

90
00:04:07,260 --> 00:04:08,100
Or maybe

91
00:04:08,580 --> 00:04:09,420
the cops

92
00:04:10,020 --> 00:04:11,300
planted an informant
inside the suppliers,

93
00:04:11,420 --> 00:04:12,700
and it led right to us.

94
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:13,940
How else

95
00:04:14,300 --> 00:04:16,020
could we get hit three times in a row?

96
00:04:16,060 --> 00:04:17,380
And every time with cops involved?

97
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:18,980
This is way too strange.

98
00:04:24,340 --> 00:04:25,660
You're all useless.

99
00:04:34,380 --> 00:04:36,020
I don't care where these people

100
00:04:36,020 --> 00:04:37,140
are from.

101
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:39,900
And I don't care what they're after.

102
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:41,420
All I know is

103
00:04:41,740 --> 00:04:43,140
I paid

104
00:04:43,860 --> 00:04:44,980
but got no goods.

105
00:04:46,580 --> 00:04:47,540
And the courier

106
00:04:47,540 --> 00:04:49,580
got taken down right at the pickup spot.

107
00:04:49,900 --> 00:04:51,180
Now the supplier keeps hounding me

108
00:04:51,180 --> 00:04:53,420
for an explanation.

109
00:04:53,860 --> 00:04:56,220
This whole mess is on you two.

110
00:04:56,660 --> 00:04:58,740
So I don't care how you do it,

111
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:00,660
you will clean this mess up.

112
00:05:01,620 --> 00:05:03,020
My goods will move

113
00:05:04,420 --> 00:05:05,660
the way they used to.

114
00:05:06,780 --> 00:05:07,620
Your lives,

115
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:09,420
and every part of you,

116
00:05:09,740 --> 00:05:10,860
are mine to hold onto for now.

117
00:05:11,180 --> 00:05:11,780
Understand?

118
00:05:12,420 --> 00:05:12,860
Understood.

119
00:05:13,820 --> 00:05:14,380
Mr. Sun,

120
00:05:15,420 --> 00:05:17,620
this is the last chance
you're giving us.

121
00:05:18,180 --> 00:05:19,420
We won't waste it.

122
00:05:19,620 --> 00:05:21,060
We'll take care of this cleanly.

123
00:05:21,100 --> 00:05:21,900
Don't worry, Mr. Sun.

124
00:05:22,820 --> 00:05:23,540
And

125
00:05:24,940 --> 00:05:25,780
about the supplier...

126
00:05:29,580 --> 00:05:31,140
Until we know what's really going on,

127
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:33,540
we're not taking in any new goods.

128
00:05:35,820 --> 00:05:37,540
You two better hurry up

129
00:05:38,420 --> 00:05:40,620
and clean up every last mess.

130
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:41,860
If you can talk it out,

131
00:05:42,220 --> 00:05:42,980
then settle it.

132
00:05:43,940 --> 00:05:44,820
If not,

133
00:05:45,740 --> 00:05:46,740
settle it another way.

134
00:05:51,540 --> 00:05:52,820
Tu, you're really playing with fire.

135
00:05:54,060 --> 00:05:55,140
When you pulled stunts before,

136
00:05:55,180 --> 00:05:57,020
our own people could cover for you.

137
00:05:57,380 --> 00:05:59,540
But this involves the task force now.

138
00:06:00,020 --> 00:06:01,500
If anything goes wrong,

139
00:06:02,180 --> 00:06:03,180
even I can't protect you.

140
00:06:05,540 --> 00:06:06,700
You know exactly

141
00:06:06,740 --> 00:06:08,180
what kind of guy Sanmahu is.

142
00:06:08,380 --> 00:06:10,940
He's a cold-blooded killer.

143
00:06:11,300 --> 00:06:13,060
I've planted an informant around him.

144
00:06:13,900 --> 00:06:15,740
He's gambling with his life.

145
00:06:17,300 --> 00:06:19,580
It's not that I don't want to
loop in Zhan Peng.

146
00:06:19,580 --> 00:06:21,100
I just don't dare.

147
00:06:21,740 --> 00:06:23,740
I don't know who that kid takes after.

148
00:06:24,140 --> 00:06:26,860
He's all about rules and principles.

149
00:06:26,860 --> 00:06:27,340
Well...

150
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:30,340
If he turns his back on me,

151
00:06:30,860 --> 00:06:32,060
and exposes my plan,

152
00:06:32,060 --> 00:06:34,060
then we're in real trouble.

153
00:06:35,180 --> 00:06:36,780
Now I get

154
00:06:37,180 --> 00:06:39,700
why you agreed to Zhan Peng's plan.

155
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:42,100
Who said I agreed to his plan?

156
00:06:42,100 --> 00:06:44,020
Don't play dumb with me!

157
00:06:44,340 --> 00:06:46,780
You backed him
when he sent Dagou out as bait

158
00:06:46,780 --> 00:06:48,980
because you're
using the same move yourself!

159
00:06:49,780 --> 00:06:51,540
I knew you were up to no good.

160
00:06:51,900 --> 00:06:52,580
No, I...

161
00:06:53,660 --> 00:06:54,940
What choice did I have?

162
00:06:55,380 --> 00:06:56,420
I couldn't say it out loud,

163
00:06:56,420 --> 00:06:57,420
but the job still had to be done.

164
00:06:58,020 --> 00:06:59,260
So I nudged him along.

165
00:07:00,380 --> 00:07:00,900
Come in.

166
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:03,660
Zhan.

167
00:07:04,180 --> 00:07:05,260
Mr. Xiong. Mr. Tu.

168
00:07:07,180 --> 00:07:08,500
Tu just briefed me

169
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:09,700
on the situation.

170
00:07:09,940 --> 00:07:11,300
Thieves stealing drugs

171
00:07:11,580 --> 00:07:12,780
is indeed unusual.

172
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:14,340
But it's not entirely impossible.

173
00:07:14,340 --> 00:07:14,860
Right?

174
00:07:15,580 --> 00:07:16,660
They've been watching that crew

175
00:07:16,660 --> 00:07:17,780
for a long time.

176
00:07:18,340 --> 00:07:20,380
We just happened to
intercept the drugs this time.

177
00:07:20,460 --> 00:07:21,420
That counts as a credit.

178
00:07:25,380 --> 00:07:26,020
Mr. Tu,

179
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:27,940
I was out of line on the platform.

180
00:07:28,780 --> 00:07:29,980
First, I should thank you.

181
00:07:29,980 --> 00:07:31,140
We owe it to you.

182
00:07:31,620 --> 00:07:33,100
Losing the drugs is no small matter.

183
00:07:33,820 --> 00:07:34,900
Then comes the question.

184
00:07:35,260 --> 00:07:35,860
Question?

185
00:07:36,420 --> 00:07:37,140
What question?

186
00:07:37,340 --> 00:07:37,860
Mr. Xiong,

187
00:07:37,860 --> 00:07:39,260
you already said it just now.

188
00:07:39,340 --> 00:07:41,100
Regarding thieves stealing drugs?

189
00:07:41,700 --> 00:07:43,020
But now the question is gone.

190
00:07:43,420 --> 00:07:44,220
Only pressure remains.

191
00:07:45,620 --> 00:07:48,060
I've drafted
a follow-up investigation plan.

192
00:07:48,660 --> 00:07:49,940
It is regarding this issue.

193
00:07:50,180 --> 00:07:51,380
Please have a look, Mr. Xiong.

194
00:07:51,900 --> 00:07:52,580
Regarding what?

195
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:55,260
The thieves stealing drugs?

196
00:07:56,580 --> 00:07:57,100
Yes.

197
00:07:57,540 --> 00:07:59,180
The core idea is simple.

198
00:07:59,420 --> 00:08:00,460
We hope Mr. Tu

199
00:08:00,540 --> 00:08:02,140
can provide more support.

200
00:08:02,540 --> 00:08:03,460
If he

201
00:08:03,620 --> 00:08:05,580
can share more details,

202
00:08:05,580 --> 00:08:07,060
it'll really help the task force.

203
00:08:07,540 --> 00:08:08,540
Please review

204
00:08:08,900 --> 00:08:09,900
the details, Mr. Xiong.

205
00:08:10,220 --> 00:08:11,460
If there's nothing else,

206
00:08:11,620 --> 00:08:12,380
I'll be leaving.

207
00:08:13,020 --> 00:08:13,740
Alright.

208
00:08:13,940 --> 00:08:15,100
Go ahead.

209
00:08:25,420 --> 00:08:27,380
Since when did this kid
change his style?

210
00:08:28,540 --> 00:08:29,900
Starting to remind me of his father.

211
00:08:30,660 --> 00:08:31,220
Mr. Sun,

212
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:33,100
their crew

213
00:08:33,860 --> 00:08:35,180
is led by that guy Sanmahu.

214
00:08:35,900 --> 00:08:37,860
He used to be a train pickpocket.

215
00:08:38,460 --> 00:08:39,140
No idea why he's

216
00:08:39,140 --> 00:08:40,820
trying to break into the drug trade now.

217
00:08:41,660 --> 00:08:42,540
Sure,

218
00:08:43,180 --> 00:08:44,700
they've got our stuff,

219
00:08:45,180 --> 00:08:46,780
but without distribution channels,

220
00:08:46,780 --> 00:08:47,900
they can't handle it.

221
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:49,580
They came to me before,

222
00:08:49,740 --> 00:08:50,820
but I blew them off.

223
00:08:51,140 --> 00:08:52,340
That's why this happened.

224
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:54,340
Forget

225
00:08:54,940 --> 00:08:57,060
how they figured out the route
we move our stuff.

226
00:08:57,300 --> 00:08:58,340
Those batches

227
00:08:58,780 --> 00:09:00,500
are cash in our hands.

228
00:09:00,780 --> 00:09:02,620
But in theirs? They're time bombs.

229
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:04,540
The more they have,

230
00:09:04,540 --> 00:09:05,540
the bigger the risk.

231
00:09:06,220 --> 00:09:07,020
So,

232
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:09,740
should we reach out to them?

233
00:09:10,020 --> 00:09:10,660
First,

234
00:09:11,260 --> 00:09:13,180
we bait them

235
00:09:13,820 --> 00:09:14,660
with our channels.

236
00:09:15,020 --> 00:09:15,780
Second,

237
00:09:16,300 --> 00:09:17,660
we see what they're really made of.

238
00:09:18,380 --> 00:09:19,580
If it works out,

239
00:09:19,940 --> 00:09:21,100
we will work together.

240
00:09:21,380 --> 00:09:22,460
If not,

241
00:09:22,540 --> 00:09:23,660
we will walk away clean.

242
00:09:25,020 --> 00:09:25,740
What do you think?

243
00:09:27,940 --> 00:09:29,300
How you handle it is your business.

244
00:09:29,940 --> 00:09:31,020
I only care about two things.

245
00:09:34,380 --> 00:09:35,500
We've got to make money.

246
00:09:36,780 --> 00:09:38,380
And we call the shots.

247
00:09:46,660 --> 00:09:47,900
I'll say this one last time.

248
00:09:49,140 --> 00:09:49,940
You've got five days

249
00:09:50,660 --> 00:09:52,300
to clean up every mess.

250
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:54,740
If you

251
00:09:55,580 --> 00:09:57,140
get any other ideas before it's done,

252
00:09:58,180 --> 00:10:00,260
this won't just be about you two.

253
00:10:01,020 --> 00:10:02,860
His blind mother

254
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:06,660
will go down with you.

255
00:10:13,900 --> 00:10:15,020
None of this

256
00:10:15,620 --> 00:10:17,220
is surprising.

257
00:10:18,220 --> 00:10:18,900
Changfeng,

258
00:10:19,620 --> 00:10:20,460
now,

259
00:10:21,180 --> 00:10:22,700
the local bosses in Xiatong

260
00:10:22,820 --> 00:10:24,860
are finally beaten down.

261
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:27,020
Now they're begging to talk.

262
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:28,340
Dou and Taohua

263
00:10:28,740 --> 00:10:29,900
deserve the credit

264
00:10:30,340 --> 00:10:31,460
for that.

265
00:10:32,380 --> 00:10:34,140
We didn't do much.

266
00:10:34,420 --> 00:10:35,820
It was

267
00:10:35,820 --> 00:10:37,180
all your planning, sir.

268
00:10:37,420 --> 00:10:38,340
Dou and I

269
00:10:39,020 --> 00:10:41,100
were just following your orders.

270
00:10:42,180 --> 00:10:43,580
Taohua knows how to talk.

271
00:10:43,580 --> 00:10:43,900
See?

272
00:10:44,380 --> 00:10:44,980
Don't worry.

273
00:10:45,260 --> 00:10:46,980
Once the distribution network

274
00:10:47,140 --> 00:10:48,380
is fully open,

275
00:10:48,580 --> 00:10:49,300
I'll make sure

276
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:50,580
everyone gets their share

277
00:10:51,140 --> 00:10:51,860
of the credit.

278
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:55,460
Victory is within reach.

279
00:11:03,940 --> 00:11:04,420
Long,

280
00:11:05,420 --> 00:11:06,260
where is this place?

281
00:11:06,260 --> 00:11:07,740
Smack dab in the middle of nowhere.

282
00:11:08,420 --> 00:11:09,740
This isn't some shady joint, is it?

283
00:11:10,380 --> 00:11:12,260
If someone gets killed here

284
00:11:12,660 --> 00:11:14,340
and dumped in the reservoir,

285
00:11:14,540 --> 00:11:15,380
no one would ever find the body.

286
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:19,660
Relax.

287
00:11:20,780 --> 00:11:22,940
They are in the business
of risking their necks.

288
00:11:22,940 --> 00:11:24,020
Meeting here makes sense.

289
00:11:40,980 --> 00:11:41,980
Dou,

290
00:11:41,980 --> 00:11:43,180
sorry I'm late.

291
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:00,340
[Favors and Loyalty]
You definitely have high standards.

292
00:12:06,380 --> 00:12:08,300
It's mealtime,
